` prefix\n\n### .gitignore\nIgnores: `node_modules/`, `dist/`, `*.tsbuildinfo`\n\n## All 12 Phase Requirements\n\n### Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n- Core queue with add/retrieve tasks in FIFO order\n- Each task: unique ID, status (\"pending\" → \"processing\"), creation timestamp\n- Retrieve oldest pending task or return null\n- Count waiting tasks\n\n### Phase 2: Named Queues\n- Multiple independent queues by name\n- Default queue if no name specified\n- Create queues implicitly on first task\n- List all queue names\n- Backward compatible with Phase 1\n\n### Phase 3: Priority\n- Priority levels 1-10 (default 5, lower = higher priority)\n- Retrieve highest-priority tasks first\n- Same priority = FIFO order\n- Invalid priorities raise error\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n\n### Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n- Delay tasks (milliseconds) or scheduled time\n- Delayed tasks only available after scheduled time\n- Non-delayed preferred over delayed\n- Multiple delayed tasks: order by availability time, priority, FIFO\n- Works with named queues\n\n### Phase 5: Retry with Backoff\n- Mark tasks completed/failed\n- Automatic retry with exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)`\n- Configurable: max retries (default 3), base delay (default 1000ms)\n- Track attempt count\n- Retried tasks keep original queue/priority\n- Failed tasks remain in failed state\n\n### Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n- Failed tasks (no retries left) → DLQ for original queue\n- View dead-lettered tasks\n- Retain error info and failure count\n- Move DLQ task back for fresh retries\n- Clear DLQ for queue\n- Each queue has independent DLQ\n\n### Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n- Specify task IDs that must complete first\n- Blocked tasks not returned until dependencies complete\n- Detect circular dependencies at creation time\n- Non-existent task dependencies cause error\n- Failed dependencies don't fail dependents (stay blocked)\n- Inspect dependency status\n\n### Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n- Per-queue max concurrency (tasks in \"processing\" state)\n- Return null if limit reached even if tasks available\n- Completing/failing task frees a slot\n- Default: unlimited\n- Query concurrency limit and current active count\n- Works with priority ordering\n\n### Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation\n- Report progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query task's current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates (cancellable)\n- Cancel pending/processing tasks\n- Pending cancelled: removed from queue\n- Processing cancelled: status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n### Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n- Schedule tasks with cron expressions\n- Supported cron formats:\n  - `*/N * * * *` - every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` - every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` - every day at midnight\n- Create/remove/list schedules\n- Manual tick mechanism (for testing)\n- Recurring tasks follow all queue rules\n\n### Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n- Per-queue middleware functions\n- Task passes through middleware stack in order\n- Middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Middleware can modify task, skip, or fail\n- Processing handler invoked after middleware\n- Each queue has independent middleware stack\n- Middleware errors mark task as failed\n\n### Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n- Stop accepting new tasks on shutdown\n- Wait for processing tasks (configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancel tasks exceeding timeout\n- Shutdown callbacks\n- Summary: completed, force-cancelled, duration\n- Safe multiple calls\n- Immediate completion if no processing tasks\n\n## Source Code Status\n\n**The `/workspace/src/` directory is empty** (contains only `.gitkeep`). You are building the task queue system from scratch, exporting your main API from `src/index.ts`.\n\nThis is a complete greenfield project where you'll incrementally build a sophisticated in-memory task queue system across 12 phases of increasing complexity."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3aa532cb77c2a46e (for resumin